Data types :

•	Data Element -  is an attribute about a person ,place or a thing containing data within a range of values
-	They describe characteristics of Activities that includes orders,transactions and events 
Data type – limits the values a data element can have.
Categories:
-	Structured data
-	Unstructured data
-	Semi-structured data
Tabular Data:
-	Data organized into a table,made up of columns and rows.
-	table represents information about a single topic.
-	Each column represents a uniquely named field within a table, also called a variable about a single characteristic.
-	The contents of each column contain values for the data element as defined by the column header.
-	Each row represents a record of a single instance of the table's topic
Database software:
-	Oracle
-	Microsoft SQL Server
-	MySQL
-	 PostgreSQL
Structured Data Types:
-	Structured data is tabular in nature and organized into rows and columns.
Unstructured  data
-	Binary
-	Audio
-	Images
-	Video
-	Large text

Character
-	The character data type limits data entry to only valid characters
-	Characters can include the alphabet and numbers.
•	Alphanumeric is the most widely used data type for storing character-based data.
Data types:
•	Numeric - integer and numeric.
•	Whole number -  presented by 0 and 1 /on and off/TRUE and FALSE
•	Rational number - numbers that include a decimal point
•	Date and Time – 
•	Currency - 
